p: United States of America Third Judicial District of Washington Territory In the matter of the complaint Martin Lawson John Strom, Christ Anderson, Thomas Steward, Ellias Krebs, Edward Haquer, John Nickels, Peter Nelson, and Victor Martinson. Marines on board the American ship or vessel "War-Hawk" for a writ of Habeaus Corpus To the Honorable Joseph R. Lewis the Judge of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory. The complaint of Martin Lawson, John Strom, Christ Anderson, Thomas Steward, John Nickels Peter Nelson, and Victor Martinson respectfully shows That the said Martin Lawson, John Strom, Christ Anderson, Thomas Steward, Ellias Krebs, Edward Haquer, John Nickels, Peter Nelson, and Victor Martinson are and each of them is unlawfully imprisioned detained confined and restrained of their Liberty. by L. V. Wyckoff Deputy United States Marshall at the city prision of the city of Seattle in King County in the Territory of Washington
